<\list>


<s1 id=ToDisplaySpecificDateTA>To Display a Specific Date or Time Period
	<idx>date, displaying<\idx>
	<idx>date format, default<\idx>
	<idx>defaults, date format<\idx>

<list order>
<item> Choose Go to Date from the View menu.
<item> Type the date you want to view in the format MM/DD/YYYY.
<item> Click Go To.
<\list>

<p indent>For information on how to change the date format, 
see <link hyperlink=CalendarOptionsDateDialog>Date Format Dialog Box<\link> 
and <xref ToCustomizeDateFormatTA>.

<newline>&empty;<newline>

<procedure>To Display Today
	<idx>Today, displaying<sort>today,displaying<\idx>
	<idx>current view<\idx>

<list bullet>
<item> Click the navigation button displaying Today or today's date.
<\list>

<p indent>Calendar changes the current view to show today
in the format you were viewing.  For example, if you are
viewing by month, choosing today's date
displays the Month view containing today.

<procedure>To Display the Previous View
	<idx>Previous view, displaying<sort>previous view, displaying<\idx>

<list bullet>
<item> Click the navigation arrow pointing left.
<\list>

<p indent>Previous view is the day, week, month, or 
year before the one you are viewing.  
For example, if you are viewing by week, the previous view 
shows the previous week.

<procedure>To Display the Next View
	<idx>Next view, displaying<sort>next view, displaying<\idx>

<list bullet>
<item> Click the navigation arrow pointing right.
<\list>

<p indent>Next view is the view after the one you are viewing.  
For example, if you are viewing by week, the next view shows the next week.

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToSpecifyACalendarViewTA>
<item> <xref CalendarGotoDateDialog>
<item> <xref ToCustomizeDateFormatTA>
<item> <xref CalendarOptionsDateDialog>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToScheduleApptTA>To Schedule a Basic Appointment
Use the Appointment Editor to insert, change, or delete
appointments on your calendar.
	<idx>appointment, scheduling<\idx>
	<idx>scheduling, basic appointment<\idx>
	<idx>appointment, inserting<\idx>
	<idx>Appointment Editor, using<sort>appointment editor, using<\idx>
	<idx>appointment, basic<\idx>
	<idx>What field, basic appointment<sort>what field, basic appointment <\idx> 

<list order>
<item>Display the Calendar view containing the day for which you 
want to schedule an appointment.

<item>Double-click that day.

<newline>&empty;<newline>

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-Sched-Appt>
<\figure>

<p>The Appointment Editor is displayed.

<item>Choose the Start and End times.

<newline>&empty;<newline>

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-Appt-Ed>
<\figure>
	<idx>appointment, default duration<\idx>
	<idx>defaults, appointment duration<\idx>

<p>The default appointment duration is one hour. If your appointment
is longer or shorter, click in the End field to edit the End time.

<item>Type a description of the appointment in the What field.

<p>For example, you may want to enter the appointment's location 
and purpose.

<p>If you want to add optional settings to an appointment,
see <xref ToSetOptionsTA>.

<item>Click Insert. 
<p>The appointment is added to your calendar.

<item>Click Cancel to close the Appointment Editor.

<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToSetOptionsTA>
<item> <xref ToSetApptEditorDefaultsTA>
<item> <xref ToSpecifyACalendarViewTA>
<item> <xref ToChangeApptTA>
<item> <xref ToDeleteApptTA>
<item> <xref ToSetUpGroupApptTA>
<item> <xref CalendarOptionsCategoryDialog>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToSetOptionsTA>To Set Appointment Options
	<idx>appointment, scheduling<\idx>
	<idx>appointment, inserting<\idx>
	<idx>scheduling, appointment<\idx>
	<idx>inserting an appointment<\idx>
	<idx>appointment, options<\idx>
	<idx>options, appointment<\idx>
	<idx>Appointment Editor, using reminders<sort>appointment editor, using reminders<\idx>
	<idx>reminders, using<\idx>
	<idx>appointment, privacy settings<\idx>
	<idx>privacy, setting<\idx>

<list order>
<item>Schedule an appointment.
<p>Follow the steps in <xref ToScheduleApptTA>.

<item>Click the More button in the Appointment Editor to 
display additional appointment options.

<newline>&empty;<newline>

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-Appt-Options>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;

<item>Select the desired appointment in the Appointment Editor list.

<item>Select Beep, Flash, Popup, or Mail for the type of reminder
you want.

<item>Edit the reminder intervals or the <emph>calendar-name@hostname<\emph> 
if necessary.

<item>Optional: To repeat the appointment more than once, choose an 
option from the Occurs menu, and then choose an option from the For menu.

<p>If you don't see the interval you want on the Occurs menu, 
choose Repeat Every and type the desired interval in days, 
weeks, or months.

<item>Choose an option from the Privacy menu.

<item>Click Change.

<item>Click Cancel to close the Appointment Editor.

<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToScheduleApptTA>
<item> <xref ToSetApptEditorDefaultsTA>
<item> <xref ToSpecifyACalendarViewTA>
<item> <xref ToChangeApptTA>
<item> <xref ToDeleteApptTA>
<item> <xref CalendarOptionsCategoryDialog>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToChangeApptTA>To Change an Appointment
	<idx>appointment, changing<\idx>
	<idx>changing an appointment<\idx>

<list order>
<item>Click the Appointment Editor icon.
<item>Select the appointment in the appointment list.
<item>Edit the appointment date, start or end time, description, 
reminders, frequency, or privacy.
<item>Click Change.
<item>Click Cancel to close the Appointment Editor.
<\list>

	<idx>Appointment Editor, clearing<sort>appointment editor, clearing<\idx>
	<idx>clearing the Appointment Editor<sort>clearing the appointment editor<\idx>
<p>Be careful if you are inserting multiple appointments, one after 
another, that you click Clear between insertions.  This will reset 
options that you may not want to carry over from one appointment to the next.

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToScheduleApptTA>
<item> <xref ToSetOptionsTA>
<item> <xref ToDeleteApptTA>
<item> <xref CalendarApptEditorDialog>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToSetUpToDoTA>To Insert a To Do Item
	<idx>To Do item, scheduling<\idx>
	<idx>scheduling, To Do item<\idx>
	<idx>To Do item, inserting<\idx>
	<idx>To Do Editor, using<\idx>

Use the To Do Editor to insert, update, or delete To Do items in your calendar.
<list order>
<item> Click the To Do Editor icon in the upper left corner of the main 
Calendar view window. 

<newline>&empty;<newline>

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-ToDoEd-Icon left>
<\figure>

<p>The To Do Editor is displayed.

<newline>&empty;<newline>

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-ToDo-Ed>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;<newline>

<item> Type or edit the due date for the To Do item in the Due Date field. 
<item> Type a description of the To Do item in the What field.
<item> Click Insert.
<item> Click Cancel to close the To Do Editor.
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToChangeToDoTA>
<item> <xref ToDeleteApptTA>
<item> <xref CalendarToDoEditorDialog>
<item> <xref ToScheduleApptTA>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToChangeToDoTA>To Change a To Do Item
	<idx>To Do item, changing<sort>to do item, changing<\idx>
	<idx>changing a To Do item<sort>changing a to do item<\idx>

<list order>
<item>Display the Calendar view containing the day for which you
want to change a To Do item.
<item>Select that day.
<item>Click the To Do Editor icon in the tool bar to open the To Do Editor.
<item>Select the To Do item in the To Do List.
<item>Edit the due date or the description of the To Do item.
<item>Select Completed to change the status of the 
To Do item, if applicable.
<item>Click Change.
<item>Click Cancel to close the To Do Editor.
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToSetUpToDoTA>
<item> <xref ToDeleteApptTA>
<item> <xref CalendarToDoEditorDialog>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToDeleteApptTA>To Delete an Appointment or To Do Item
	<idx>appointment, deleting<\idx>
	<idx>deleting an appointment<\idx>
	<idx>To Do item, deleting<sort>to do item, deleting<\idx>
	<idx>deleting a To Do item<sort>deleting a to do item<\idx>

<list order>
<item>Click the Appointment or To Do Editor icon.
<item>Select the appointment or To Do item in the appropriate list.
<item>Click Delete.
<item>Click Cancel to close the editor.
<\list>

