<s1 id=ToFindApptTA>To Find an Appointment in Your Calendar
	<idx>appointment, finding<\idx>
	<idx>finding an appointment in your calendar<\idx>
	<idx>defaults, find search range<\idx>
<list order>
<item>Choose Find from the View menu.
<item>In the Find field, type some text that can become a keyword for the 
search; for example, <computer>Dentist<\computer> or 
<computer>Conference<\computer>.
<p>The Find field is not case-sensitive.
<p>By default, Calendar searches the past and future six months in your
calendar.
If you want to change the search range, select Search all or edit the dates
in the Search from fields.
<item>Click Find.
<p>The appointments with matching text are displayed in the Find window.
<item>Select the desired appointment in the list.
<item>Click Show Appointment to display the entire appointment.
<item>Click Cancel to close the Find dialog box.
<\list>


<s1 id=ToAddUsersCalendarTA>To Add or Delete Calendars in the Browse List
	<idx>calendars, browsing<\idx>
	<idx>browsing calendars<\idx>
	<idx>Browse Menu Editor, using<sort>browse menu editor, using<\idx>
	<idx>Browse List, adding calendars to<sort>browse list, adding calendars to<\idx>

<procedure>To add a calendar to the Browse list:
	<idx>Browse List, adding calendars to<sort>browse list, adding calendars to<\idx>
	<idx>adding calendars to Browse list<sort>adding calendars to browse list<\idx>
	<idx>calendars, adding to Browse list<sort>calendars, adding to browse list<\idx>
<list order>
<item>Choose Menu Editor from the Browse menu. 
<item>Type the <emph>user-name@hostname<\emph> in the User Name field.
<item>Click Add Name.
<item>To erase your changes and leave the dialog box displayed, click Reset.
<item>To save your changes and close the dialog box, click OK.
<item>To save your changes and leave the dialog box displayed, click Apply.
<item>To erase your changes and close the dialog box, click Cancel.
<p>Saving changes adds the calendar to the Browse menu in the menu bar.
<\list>

<procedure>To delete a calendar from the Browse list:
	<idx>Browse List, deleting names from<sort>browse list, deleting names from<\idx>
	<idx>deleting calendars from the Browse list<sort>deleting calendars from the browse list<\idx>
	<idx>calendars, deleting from the Browse list<sort>calendars, deleting from the browse list<\idx>
	<idx>Reset, using<sort>reset, using<\idx>

<list order>
<item> Select a calendar name in the Browse list.
<item> Click Remove Name.
<item>To erase your changes and leave the dialog box displayed, click Reset. 
<item>To save your changes and close the dialog box, click OK.
<item>To save your changes and leave the dialog box displayed, click Apply.
<item>To erase your changes and close the dialog box, click Cancel.
<p>Saving changes deletes the calendar from the Browse menu in the menu bar.
<\list>

