<s1 id=ToCompareMultipleUsersCalendarsTA>To Compare Multiple Calendars
	<idx>calendars, comparing<\idx>
	<idx>comparing calendars<\idx>

<list order>
<item> Choose Compare Calendars from the Browse menu.
<p> The Compare Calendars dialog box is displayed.
The first time you open this dialog box, only your calendar
is displayed in the grid.
<p> To add other calendars to the Browse list, see
<xref ToAddUsersCalendarTA>.
<item> Select entries in the Browse list.
	<idx>compare calendars grid, using<\idx>
	<idx>grid, Compare Calendars<sort>grid, compare calendars<\idx>

<p> The Compare Calendars grid changes to add the new calendar, overlaying
all displayed calendars.
The lightest areas on the grid indicate free times; the darkest
areas are busy times.
<p> Use this grid to identify times available for a group
appointment.
<\list>
<procedure> To change the time interval displayed in the grid:
<list bullet>
<item> Choose an option from the Compare Calendars Go To menu
<p> <emph>Or<\emph>
<item> Type the date you want to view in the Go To field
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToAddUsersCalendarTA>
<item> <xref ToDisplayAnotherUsersCalendarTA>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToSetUpGroupApptTA>To Schedule a Group Appointment
	<idx>group appointment, selecting day and time<\idx>
	<idx>appointment, group<\idx>
	<idx>compare calendars grid, using<\idx>
	<idx>grid, Compare Calendars<sort>grid, compare calendars<\idx>
	<idx>group appointment, scheduling<\idx>
	<idx>scheduling, group appointment<\idx>
	<idx>Group Appointment Editor, opening<sort>group appointment editor, opening<\idx>

If you want to set up a regular appointment, see 
<xref ToScheduleApptTA>.

<!--Use the Group Appointment Editor to insert, change, or delete group -->
<!--appointments on your and other calendars.  Even if you don't -->
<!--have insert access to other calendars, you can use the Group Appointment  -->
<!--Editor to mail notices of group appointments to other users. -->
<list order>
<item>Choose Compare Calendars from the Browse menu.
<item>Select one or more entries in the Browse list.
<item>Click in the grid on a time block for which you want to set up a 
group appointment.  Unshaded blocks represent potentially available times.
<p>The time block is highlighted.
<p>A busy character (asterisk) is displayed next to a calendar name in the 
Browse list if the proposed appointment would conflict.
<item>Click Schedule to open the Group Appointment Editor.
<p> The Group Appointment Editor is displayed with the fields for 
date, time, and mail automatically filled out.
<item>Type (or edit) the group appointment start time in the Start field.
<item>Type (or edit) the group appointment end time in the End field.
<item>Type the appointment description, such as its location or purpose,
in the What field.
<item>Optional: Click More to choose the repeat interval and duration 
for the group appointment.
<item>Click Insert to add the group appointment to the selected
calendars.
<p> If you don't have insert access on all the calendars, you may want to
send mail to notify others in the group about the group appointment.  See 
<xref ToMailRemindersToGroupTA>.
<item> Click Cancel to close the Group Appointment Editor.
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToScheduleApptTA>
<item> <xref ToMailRemindersToGroupTA>
<item> <xref ToGrantAccessToOtherUsersTA>
<item> <xref CalendarCompareCalsDialog>
<item> <xref CalendarGroupApptEditorDialog>
<\list>


<s1 id=ToMailRemindersToGroupTA>To Mail Reminders to the Group
	<idx>group appointment, mail reminders<\idx>
	<idx>Group Appointment Editor, mailing reminders<sort>group appointment editor, mailing reminders<\idx>
	<idx>mail reminders, of group appointment<\idx>
	<idx>reminders (mail), of group appointment<\idx>

Once you've set up a group appointment (date, start and end times,
description, repeat interval), you may want to mail
the group a reminder.  To send mail:
<list order>
<item> Click Mail in the Group Appointment Editor.
<p> Calendar displays a Compose window containing an appointment
attachment.  The appointment attachment is pre-addressed to the 
selected users and automatically filled out with the date and 
appointment start and end times.
<item> Click Deliver in the Compose window.
<p> Calendar mails the reminder to the selected users.
<p> Recipients of a mail message with a calendar-formatted 
reminder can drag the message from the Mailer header window
and drop it on their calendars to automatically schedule the 
pre-formatted appointment.
<\list>

<procedure>See Also
<list bullet tight>
<item> <xref ToSetUpGroupApptTA>
<item> <xref ToDetermineAccessToOtherCalendarsTA>
<item> <xref CalendarGroupApptEditorDialog>
