	<idx>granting access to your calendar by others<\idx>
	<idx>browse access<\idx>
	<idx>insert access, granting to your calendar by others<\idx>
	<idx>delete access, granting to your calendar by others<\idx>
	<idx>defaults, user access<\idx>
	<idx>Access List and Permissions dialog box, using<sort>access list and permissions dialog box, using<\idx>
	<idx>Reset, using<sort>reset, using<\idx>
	<idx>world access <\idx> 
	<idx>access, world <\idx> 
	<idx>username, calendar access <\idx> 

<list order>
<item>Choose Options from the File menu.
<item>Choose Access List and Permissions from the Category menu.
<p>The Access List and Permissions dialog box is displayed.

<newline>&empty;

<note>Depending on the version of Calendar you have, you'll see one
of the following Access List and Permissions dialog boxes.  Use the procedure
that matches the version you have.
<\note>

<newline>&empty;

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-Access>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;

<item>In the User Name field, type <emph>username@hostname<\emph> 
for the user to whom you want to grant access. To grant access to
everyone, type <computer>world<\computer> in the User Name field.
<note>The default permission is for browse (view) access only.
Individual user access overrides world access; if everyone (world) has
browse access and user X has browse and insert access, user X can
browse and insert entries in the current calendar. <\note>
<item>Select any combination of Browse, Insert, and Delete permissions.
<item>Click Add Name to add <emph>username<\emph> or
everyone (<computer>world<\computer>) to the Access list with the
permissions you've chosen.
<item>To erase your changes and leave the dialog box displayed, click Reset. 
<item>To save your changes and close the dialog box, click OK.
<item>To save your changes and leave the dialog box displayed, click Apply.
<item>To erase your changes and close the dialog box, click Cancel.
<p>Saving changes grants the selected access to the specified user. 
<\list>

<emph>Or:<\emph>
<list order>
<item>Choose Options from the File menu.
<item>Choose Access List and Permissions from the Category menu.
<p>The Access List and Permissions dialog box is displayed.

<newline>&empty;<newline>

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-Access-Alternate>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;

<item>In the User Name field, type <emph>username@hostname<\emph>
for the user to whom you want to grant access. To grant access to
everyone, type <computer>world<\computer> in the User Name field.
<note>The default permission is for view access to public appointments only.
Individual user access overrides world access; if everyone (world) has
view access and user X has view and insert access, user X can
view and insert entries in the current calendar. <\note>
<item>Select any combination of View, Insert, and Change permissions, and Public,
Semiprivate, or Private access rights.
<p>Permissions control whether others can perform specific 
operations on your calendar.  You can choose more than one permission.

<p>Access rights control the specific types of appointments others can see.
<item>Click Add to add <emph>username<\emph> or
everyone (<computer>world<\computer>) to the Access list with the 
permissions and access rights you've chosen.
<item>To erase your changes and leave the dialog box displayed, click Reset.
<item>To save your changes and close the dialog box, click OK.
<item>To save your changes and leave the dialog box displayed, click Apply.
<item>To erase your changes and close the dialog box, click Cancel.
<p>Saving changes grants the selected access and permissions to the 
specified user.
<\list>

