<s1 id=ToCustomizePrinterSettingsTA>To Customize Printer Settings
	<idx>printer settings, customizing<\idx>
	<idx>customizing printer settings<\idx>

<p>Calendar uses the default printer settings when you choose Print
Current View from the File menu.
<procedure>To Change Printer Settings for a Single Print Job
<newline>&empty;
<list order>
<item>Choose Print from the File menu.
<p>The Print dialog box is displayed.
<item>Double-click in the Printer Name field to select the contents and 
type the new printer name.
<item>Click the arrows next to the Copies field to adjust the number of
copies to be printed, or type the number.
<item>Choose a Calendar view to Print from the Report Type menu.
<item>Optional: Change the range of time to print in the From or To fields.
<item>Optional: Add printer options in the Print Command Options field.
<p>For example, to save paper, you may want to specify 
<computer>-o nobanner<\computer> to suppress header pages.
<item>To print Calendar data to a file, select Print to file.
<p>If necessary, click again on this setting to deselect it.
<item>Edit the file name, if desired.
<item>Click Print.
<\list>

<procedure>To Customize Printer Settings for All Future Jobs
<newline>&empty;
<list order>
<item>Choose Options from the File menu.
<item>Choose Printer Settings from the Category menu.
<p> The Printer Settings dialog box is displayed.
<item>Select the Printer setting.
<item>Edit the Options field to specify print command line options if any.
<p>For example, to save paper, you may want to specify 
<computer>-o nobanner<\computer> to suppress header pages.
<item>Edit the page dimensions or position if necessary.
<item>Edit the number of units if desired.  
<p>For example, if you are printing
Week view and you set Units to 2, you will print the current week and the
next week.
<item>Edit the number of copies if you want more than one.
<item>Choose the desired privacy option for the information you want printed.
<item>To erase your changes and leave the dialog box displayed, click Reset.
<item>To save your changes and close the dialog box, click OK.
<item>To save your changes and leave the dialog box displayed, click Apply.
<item>To erase your changes and close the dialog box, click Cancel.
<\list>

